  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Chen et al. (2018) developed an effective model using adversarial networks for super-resolution generation to enhance the visual impact of underwater images in target/object detection and recognition tasks.",
    "Sun et al. (2018) introduced an underwater object detection model based on CNNs.",
    "In particular, they were able to discriminate targets in low-contrast underwater images by incorporating a weighted probability decision mechanism.",
    "Target/object state changes and occlusion also significantly impact the target detection process.",
    "Lin et al. (2020) proposed a method called RoIMix, which exhibited improved generalization performance, especially for detecting underwater images with overlap, occlusion, and blur."
  ],
